1
00:00:03,753 --> 00:00:07,084
Sometimes they’re together
as one—Mahāprabhu,

2
00:00:07,084 --> 00:00:10,300
then apart—Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa,
together as Mahāprabhu.

3
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:14,470
Gaura-līlā and Kṛṣṇa-līlā are running
in parallel eternally.

4
00:00:14,470 --> 00:00:16,462
Which is first?

5
00:00:16,462 --> 00:00:20,107
Guru Mahārāj says, “The gift or the giver?

6
00:00:20,178 --> 00:00:22,754
[The Giver and the Gift]

7
00:00:24,001 --> 00:00:26,963
Mahāprabhu is the giver.

8
00:00:28,261 --> 00:00:31,642
Which comes first, the gift or the giver?

9
00:00:31,642 --> 00:00:33,775
He’s gifting Kṛṣṇa-līlā;

10
00:00:33,775 --> 00:00:39,288
yathā yathā gaura-padāravinde
vindeta bhaktiṁ kṛta-puṇya-rāśiḥ

11
00:00:39,288 --> 00:00:48,674
tathā tathotsarpati hṛdy akasmāt
rādhā-padāmbhoja-sudhāṁśu-rāśiḥ
(Śrī Chaitanya-chandramrta: 88)

12
00:00:52,730 --> 00:00:54,767
Guru Mahārāj will say,

13
00:00:54,767 --> 00:01:00,890
“Vṛndāvan is for the highest section
of liberated souls,

14
00:01:00,890 --> 00:01:04,626
that’s why Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh
was established

15
00:01:04,641 --> 00:01:08,350
in Nabadwīp Dhām, in Gupta Govardhan.

16
00:01:08,479 --> 00:01:12,222
Vṛndāvan is for the highest section
of liberated souls;

17
00:01:12,222 --> 00:01:18,605
kṛṣṇa-līlāmṛta-sāra, tāra śata śata dhāra, 
daśa-dike vahe yāhā haite (Cc: 2.25.271).

18
00:01:18,605 --> 00:01:24,032
What is the difference between
Kṛṣṇa-līlā and Gaura-līlā?

19
00:01:25,452 --> 00:01:29,258
Kṛṣṇa-līlā … if it’s only meant for

20
00:01:29,258 --> 00:01:31,147
the highest section of liberated souls,

21
00:01:31,147 --> 00:01:34,934
that means how many are excluded?

22
00:01:36,417 --> 00:01:38,383
What is Gaura-līlā?

23
00:01:38,383 --> 00:01:42,111
The magnanimous distribution of Kṛṣṇa-līlā.

24
00:01:42,111 --> 00:01:46,684
Kṛṣṇa-līlā—madhurya. Gaura-līlā—audārya.

25
00:01:46,684 --> 00:01:51,410
Distributing that daśa-dike
—means ten directions,

26
00:01:51,410 --> 00:01:56,255
North, South, East, West,
up, down, etc.—

27
00:01:57,757 --> 00:02:00,148
So, what is generally reserved for

28
00:02:00,148 --> 00:02:02,778
the highest section of liberated souls

29
00:02:02,778 --> 00:02:06,286
is being extended
to the non-liberated section.

30
00:02:06,286 --> 00:02:09,152
That’s another way of putting it.

31
00:02:09,152 --> 00:02:12,034
So what does Prabodhānanda say?

32
00:02:12,034 --> 00:02:16,304
Aṣṭa-sakhī Tuṅga-vidyā should know;

33
00:02:16,304 --> 00:02:23,404
he says, “Give your
full attention to Gaura-pād,

34
00:02:23,404 --> 00:02:26,156
the lotus feet of Mahāprabhu.”

35
00:02:26,156 --> 00:02:27,997
Nityānanda says, “Bhājā-gaurāṅga.”

36
00:02:27,997 --> 00:02:30,220
They’re trying to tell us

37
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:33,653
how to get entrance into that plane.

38
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:38,025
Give your full attention
to the lotus feet of Mahāprabhu.

39
00:02:38,025 --> 00:02:40,920
Vindeta bhaktiṁ kṛta-puṇya-rāśiḥ

40
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:46,019
means, those who are sukṛtivān, su-medhasā,

41
00:02:46,019 --> 00:02:49,030
refined theistic intellect,

42
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:52,318
they’ll see the entrance to Vṛndāvan
is in Nabadwīp,

43
00:02:52,318 --> 00:02:57,239
the entrance into Kṛṣṇa-līlā is Gaura-līlā.

44
00:02:57,690 --> 00:02:59,683
And what will happen?

45
00:02:59,683 --> 00:03:04,489
It says, If you do that …
Because who is Mahāprabhu?

46
00:03:04,489 --> 00:03:07,500
Śrī Chaitanya Rādhā Kṛṣṇa
nahi anya (Guru-paramparā: 6);

47
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,941
Rādhā-bhāva-dyuti-suvalitam (Cc: 1.1.5);

48
00:03:09,941 --> 00:03:13,152
Kṛṣṇa enveloped in the
heart and halo of Rādhārāṇī,

49
00:03:13,152 --> 00:03:15,971
then, tathā tathotsarpati hṛdy akasmāt,

50
00:03:15,971 --> 00:03:20,354
automatically, subconsciously, deep
within the core of your heart,

51
00:03:20,354 --> 00:03:25,483
what will appear?
Rādhā-rasa-sudhā-nidhi,

52
00:03:27,544 --> 00:03:32,460
the nectarean ocean of service
to the lotus feet of Śrīmati Rādhārāṇī,

53
00:03:32,460 --> 00:03:36,463
that flow will come to your heart

54
00:03:36,463 --> 00:03:43,097
and you’ll find yourself awakening
in the soil of Vṛndāvan.

55
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:46,484
And Guru Mahārāj gave one comparison,

56
00:03:46,484 --> 00:03:50,881
“If you get on the flight in New York,

57
00:03:50,881 --> 00:03:55,263
and you get off in India.”

58
00:03:57,171 --> 00:04:00,361
That’s one example he gave.

59
00:04:00,361 --> 00:04:02,521
Another example he said is like a machine;

60
00:04:02,521 --> 00:04:04,424
you put the coin in here,

61
00:04:04,424 --> 00:04:08,398
and the ticket comes out on the other side.

62
00:04:08,398 --> 00:04:11,292
You put your coin, your serving capital,

63
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:13,118
in the lotus feet of Mahāprabhu,

64
00:04:13,118 --> 00:04:18,487
and collect your ticket for Vṛndāvan. 

